# .clinerules — Cline Operational Rules

## Session Lifecycle
- **Start**: Read `activeContext.md`. Only read `projectContext.md`/`decisionLog.md`/`progress.md` if task requires full history.
- **DO NOT** re-read `AGENTS.md` — it is already in your system prompt.
- **End**: Update memory bank with new decisions/patterns/gotchas. Document bugs in protected files to `BACKLOG.md` instead of editing.

## MCP Usage
- **Context7**: Fetch current docs before writing code touching external libraries (Playwright, Streamlit, pytest, uv, ruff, mypy).
- **Memory Bank**: Files at project root. Use native file writing (not MCP tools).

## Debugging
- **Preferred**: `notebooks/debug_pipeline.ipynb` for placeholder/scraper issues.
- **Fallback**: `scripts/debug/debug_pipeline.py`.
- **E2E**: `scripts/uat/uat_automationexercise.py` after placeholder fixes.

## Terminal Rules
- Git Bash (MINGW64) on Windows. Forward slashes only. POSIX commands only (`cat`, `ls`, `grep`).
- Use python one-liners for complex text processing to avoid shell escaping bugs.

## Discipline
- One feature per session. Never declare done without end-to-end verification.
- Always: `ruff` → `mypy` → `pytest` → human reviews diff → commit.